<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Mananut Bhread on 06-06-2002 05:06 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">You know I keep seeing people say that clerics need new spells, items, effects, etc. in order to function well in the experience portion of EverQuest today... what about alternate methods of increasing our desirability without adding new spells or items available to us...

Let me outline where I'm going here.  Two and a half years ago, no one would have thought of doing Sol B without a cleric in their KPC party.  Just wouldn't have been thought of.  Nowadays with items like Fungi and weapons like Centi SS / LS, Lamentation (and these are just the crappy ones), players regen health so fast and kill the mbos so quickly, you can get by with say, two druids, instead of a cleric, or a druid and a shaman.

Why not make a zone that's a little bit above our now beloved Accursed Temple of Cazic-Thule, something that absolutely without question requires a cleric to do.  And make the rewards exceptional.  Not necessarily in terms of loot, but in terms of experience.  What if we were to revamp Najena (arguably deserted on most any server) or Befallen (again, another deserted wasted zone).  These zones are CLOSE to city areas.  They are not being used though.  What if the mobs in just the entry way were hitting for 250... and what if you got a half a blue of experience just dropping an entryway mob... with mobs in the depth of the dungeons giving up to a full blue per kill.  You could increase the demand for a cleric while also giving good experience.

I think as time passed and employees left Verant, no one bothered to explain to the new exployees a simple fact that should be obvious:  In order to encourage someone to group, every member of the group needs to gain more experience than they could possibly gain solo.  That means if you want to entice a monk to come, if that monk makes a yellow per hour soloing, he needs to make a yellow every 30 to 40 minutes in this group.  Lets face it... for the majority of us at level 60, the loot we [b]really[/b] want is only obtainable through a large & powerful guild.  Gaining AAXP points is a clear increase in power which helps along that goal...

Without adding a lot of new gear or abilities or spells, I just don't see a way for us as a clerics to be more desired in groups or to solo... and I'm not sure the answer is soloing... I think the answer should be to make more zones that [i]require[/i] a cleric in your group.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
</table>

